Your task is to caption images for a museum catalog. Each caption should succinctly capture the essence of the image, formatted to highlight important keywords. Include the following elements in your caption:

- Subject of the image
- Facial features of the subject (e.g., eye color, hair color)
- Action occurring in the image 
- Mood or tone of the image 
- Style of the image (e.g., modern, classical)
- Type of image (e.g., photograph, painting, sculpture)
- Relevant objects within the image 
- Description of the background scene 
- Additional relevant details pertained to the image.  

Keep phrases concise, limiting filler words, and separate different elements with commas only. Focus on clarity and relevance in your captions. Respond only with the caption.